This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing (NLP) applied to the domain of biology. The use of text mining tools to extract key biological information suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The focus on information extraction and the use of a generic text processor suggests that it could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a corpus and evaluation metrics suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the application of NLP techniques to extract biological information suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
